            <h1>The Intelligent Games: How AI Rebuilt the 2026 Winter Olympics</h1>
            <p class="post-meta">Curated by <strong>Coltan Wilkie</strong> | February 14, 2026</p>
        </header>

        <article class="full-post">
            <p class="intro-text">
                The "Cloud Olympics" are over. At the Milano Cortina 2026 Games, we have officially entered the era of the <strong>Intelligent Olympics</strong>. For the first time in history, the boundary between an athleteâ€™s physical movement and digital data has completely dissolved, transforming the Games into a living, breathing AI laboratory. From "gut-feeling" judging to biomechanical "Digital Twins," the tech stack behind this yearâ€™s medals is as impressive as the athletes themselves.
            </p>

            <div class="jump-menu">
